    <h4>Description:</h4>
    <p>Samosa is a classic Indian snack featuring a crispy, flaky pastry filled with spicy mashed potatoes and peas. It's perfect with tea or as a party snack.</p>

    <h4>Prep Time:</h4>
    <p>‚è±Ô∏è <strong>30 minutes</strong></p>

    <h4>Ingredients:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>2 cups all-purpose flour (maida)</li>
        <li>3 boiled potatoes (mashed)</li>
        <li>1/2 cup green peas</li>
        <li>1 tsp cumin seeds</li>
        <li>1 tsp garam masala</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp turmeric powder</li>
        <li>1 tsp coriander powder</li>
        <li>1 green chili (chopped)</li>
        <li>Salt to taste</li>
        <li>Oil for frying and kneading</li>
        <li>Water as needed</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Instructions:</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>Mix flour, salt, and 2 tbsp oil. Add water gradually to form a stiff dough. Let it rest for 20 minutes.</li>
        <li>Heat 1 tbsp oil in a pan. Add cumin seeds and green chili. Saut√© for a minute.</li>
        <li>Add turmeric, coriander powder, mashed potatoes, peas, garam masala, and salt. Mix well and cook for 3‚Äì4 mins. Cool the filling.</li>
        <li>Divide dough into small balls. Roll each into an oval shape and cut in half.</li>
        <li>Form a cone with each half, fill with potato mixture, and seal the edges with water.</li>
        <li>Deep fry the samosas on medium heat until golden and crispy.</li>
        <li>Serve hot with green chutney or tamarind sauce.</li>
    </ol>
